The word comes from Sanskrit:

“Purna” = full or complete
“Ma” / “Masi” = moon

So, Purnima = Full Moon 🌕

On this day, the Moon appears completely bright because the Earth is between the Sun and Moon, and sunlight fully lights the Moon.

